PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari has assured that Nigeria will partner further with Ukraine to the benefit of both countries. The President spoke at State House, Abuja, Tuesday, while receiving in farewell audience the outgoing Ambassador of Ukraine, His Excellency Dr Valeril Aleksandruk, who had spent over four years in Nigeria. A statement issued by Femi Adesina, Special Adviser to the President (Media and Publicity), informed that Ukraine currently collaborates with Nigeria in the areas of education, military cooperation, space exploration, and many others. ALSO READ:  BREAKING: 7 PDP gov aspirants in Kogi step down for Wada as party set for pry election Oyo contractor promises January to deliver 10,000 metric… Nigerians call for economic boycott of South Africa… Ebonyi govt offers rent-free shops to traders at … FG targets 15m children in school feeding programme ―… It quoted the outgoing Ambassador as saying: “There are almost 5,000 Nigerians currently studying in Ukraine. And the number increases every year. Education is a great investment for the future.” Dr Aleksandruk added that his country also supplies Nigeria military hardware and ammunition, particularly to fight insurgency, and also informed that two agreements have been signed by the countries on space exploration. “We are ready for a new level in bilateral relations,” the Ambassador submitted. President Buhari wished him well in further assignments his country would give him. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
